The composition and copyrights of Hangul-ucs package

The Hangul-ucs package is composed of four parts.
 1. dhucs -- a LaTeX style package to typeset Korean Language
 2. fonts-unttf -- the font package of UnFonts to use with dhucs
 3. fonts-uhc-unicode -- the font package of UHC fonts to use with dhucs
 4. fonts-trivcj -- the font package of Chinese/Japanese CID fonts to use with dhucs

Any of these three font-(sub)packages does not contain truetype/type1 font files in itself.
Only TeX-metrics(.tfm), map files(.map) and supplementary files are present.
The real truetype/opentype/type1 fonts can be found at their distribution sites,
that is:
 1. UnFonts truetype : http://kldp.net/projects/unfonts/
 2. UHC type 1 fonts : http://project.ktug.or.kr/hlatex/

